  "steps_en": [
   "Macerate angelica root, sweet orange peel, Ceylon cinnamon, and cloves in 5 L of 75° spirit for 5 days.",
   "Decant after 5 days.",
   "Mix the resulting tincture (450 g) with 12.5 g of 95° spirit, 2 g genuine cognac, 2 g simple syrup, 4 g wine syrup, and 6 g water.",
   "Colour with saffron tincture, adding gradually to avoid the extract flavour becoming too dominant."
  ],
  "notes_en": "This is an excellent imitation of the liqueur made by the Benedettines of Fécamp. The flavour of the extract should not be overpowering; it is best added little by little. If 450 g of tincture is insufficient, a little more may be added. The most suitable wine for making the syrup is Sardinian or Polcevera wine made from ripe grapes.",
